<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Programming note:</strong> <em>Money S=
tuff will be off tomorrow, back on Monday.</em></p><table class=3D"header" =
width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">OpenSea insider trading</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A famous fact of US securities law is =
that there is no law against insider trading. What there is is a law agains=
t securities fraud: It is illegal =E2=80=9Cto employ any device, scheme, or=
 artifice to defraud=E2=80=9D someone in connection with a securities trade=
.[1] For a long time courts have interpreted that to include insider tradin=
g, and there is a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
27923003.286612/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubGF3LmNvcm5lbGwuZWR1L2Nmci90ZXh0LzE3LzI0MC4=
xMGI1LTE/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB634e230a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscop=
e=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Securities and Exchange=
 Commission rule</a>=C2=A0clarifying that in fact insider trading counts as=
 a scheme or artifice to defraud. But there is no law against insider tradi=
ng specifically; instead, insider trading is a=C2=A0type of fraud.</p><p st=
yle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It is a weird type of fraud: If an executive of a p=
ublic company trades on inside information about her company, she is defrau=
ding shareholders, to whom she has a fiduciary duty. (This is called =E2=80=
=9Cclassical=E2=80=9D insider trading.) If the executive tells her therapis=
t about an upcoming merger, and the therapist trades on that knowledge, the=
 therapist is betraying the executive, to whom he has a =E2=80=9C<a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27923003.286612/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
d3cubGF3LmNvcm5lbGwuZWR1L2Nmci90ZXh0LzE3LzI0MC4xMGI1LTI/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cBa3cb9612" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;">duty of trust or confidence</a>,=E2=80=9D and that =
betrayal=C2=A0<em>plus=C2=A0</em>the therapist=E2=80=99s trading also count=
s as fraud.=C2=A0(This is called =E2=80=9Cmisappropriation=E2=80=9D insider=
 trading.) My shorthand is that =E2=80=9Cinsider trading is not about fairn=
ess, it=E2=80=99s about theft=E2=80=9D: If you have some duty to someone to=
 keep=C2=A0nonpublic information secret, and you trade on that information,=
 then you have committed insider trading. You have committed securities fra=
ud.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Now, insider trading is a type of=C2=A0=
<em>securities=C2=A0</em>fraud. But there is another federal statute that m=
akes it a crime to use =E2=80=9Cany scheme or artifice to defraud=E2=80=9D =
someone using a phone or the internet.[2] This crime is generally called =
=E2=80=9Cwire fraud,=E2=80=9D and it is much broader than securities fraud.=
 Securities fraud is doing fraud about securities. Wire fraud is doing frau=
d about=C2=A0<em>absolutely anything</em>, as long as you do the fraud usin=
g email or the phone or text messages or a chat app, and in 2022 you certai=
nly do. So every fraud is wire fraud.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You m=
ight put these things together and conclude: If insider trading in securiti=
es is securities fraud, then insider trading in=C2=A0<em>anything=C2=A0</em=
>is wire fraud. If insider trading =E2=80=94=C2=A0using information from so=
meone else, to whom you have a duty to keep it confidential, to buy for you=
r own account =E2=80=94=C2=A0is a =E2=80=9Cdevice, scheme, or artifice to d=
efraud=E2=80=9D under securities law, then surely it is also a =E2=80=9Csch=
eme or artifice to defraud=E2=80=9D under wire-fraud law. If you buy real e=
state based on insider knowledge of where Amazon.com Inc. is going to put i=
ts new headquarters, and you had some duty to Amazon to keep that knowledge=
 private, maybe that is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/=
click/27923003.286612/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9zdGF0ZS1zZW5hd=
G9yLXByb3Bvc2VzLWxhdy10by1iYW4tcmVhbC1lc3RhdGUtZGVhbHMtYmFzZWQtb24tbm9ucHVi=
bGljLWluZm9ybWF0aW9uLTE1NDM4NDIwMDA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1afb0629" item=
prop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color=
: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bord=
er-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #cc=
c;">insider trading in real estate</a>. If you make sports bets based on in=
sider knowledge of some star player=E2=80=99s injury or trade demands, and =
you had some duty to that player to keep that knowledge private,=C2=A0maybe=
 that is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27923003.=
286612/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjAtMDUt=
MDYvaW5zaWRlci10cmFkaW5nLW9uLXNvY2Nlci10cmFkZXM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDYwMjIyX01PTkV=
ZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09Mj=
IwNjAyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5c325422" i=
temprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: =
#ccc;"> insider trading in sports bets</a>. And <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27923003.286612/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuanVzdGljZS5nb=
3YvdXNhby1zZG55L3ByL2Zvcm1lci1lbXBsb3llZS1uZnQtbWFya2V0cGxhY2UtY2hhcmdlZC1m=
aXJzdC1ldmVyLWRpZ2l0YWwtYXNzZXQtaW5zaWRlci10cmFkaW5nLXNjaGVtZQ/607f07ceef4b=
8524a319a23cB4739f678" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targe=
t=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bor=
der-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: s=
olid; background-color: #ccc;">of course</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">Damian Williams, the United States Attorney for the Southern=
 District of New York, and Michael J. Driscoll, Assistant Director-in-Charg=
e of the New York Field Office of the Federal Bureau of Investigation (=E2=
=80=9CFBI=E2=80=9D), announced [Wednesday] the unsealing of an Indictment c=
harging NATHANIEL CHASTAIN, a former product manager at Ozone Networks, Inc=
. d/b/a OpenSea (=E2=80=9COpenSea=E2=80=9D), with wire fraud and money laun=
dering in connection with a scheme to commit insider trading in Non-Fungibl=
e Tokens, or =E2=80=9CNFTs,=E2=80=9D by using confidential information abou=
t what NFTs were going to be featured on OpenSea=E2=80=99s homepage for his=
 personal financial gain. =C2=A0...</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">U.S. At=
torney Damian Williams said: =C2=A0=E2=80=9CNFTs might be new, but this typ=
e of criminal scheme is not. =C2=A0As alleged, Nathaniel Chastain betrayed =
OpenSea by using its confidential business information to make money for hi=
mself. =C2=A0Today=E2=80=99s charges demonstrate the commitment of this Off=
ice to stamping out insider trading =E2=80=93 whether it occurs on the stoc=
k market or the blockchain.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">FBI As=
sistant Director-in-Charge Michael J. Driscoll said: =C2=A0=E2=80=9CIn this=
 case, as alleged, Chastain launched an age-old scheme to commit insider tr=
ading by using his knowledge of confidential information to purchase dozens=
 of NFTs in advance of them being featured on OpenSea=E2=80=99s homepage. W=
ith the emergence of any new investment tool, such as blockchain supported =
non-fungible tokens, there are those who will exploit vulnerabilities for t=
heir own gain. The FBI will continue to aggressively pursue actors who choo=
se to manipulate the market in this way.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It=E2=80=99s a novel approach, but you see their point=
. NFTs don=E2=80=99t have to be securities for insider trading in them to b=
e wire fraud. On the other hand, I guess you can see Chastain=E2=80=99s poi=
nt? It=C2=A0<em>is=C2=A0</em>a novel approach. Arguably Chastain (allegedly=
) invented NFT insider trading; how could have he have known it was wire fr=
aud? Anyway <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/279230=
03.286612/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuanVzdGljZS5nb3YvdXNhby1zZG55L3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvZ=
mlsZS8xNTA5NzAxL2Rvd25sb2Fk/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB86a14ec5" itemprop=3D"=
StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #00000=
0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">here=
=E2=80=99s the indictment</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
OpenSea is an NFT marketplace, where users can create, sell, and buy NFTs. =
Beginning in or about May 2021, the top of the homepage of OpenSea=E2=80=99=
s website started displaying featured NFTs. OpenSea changed the featured NF=
T multiple times per week. Information about what NFT and was going to be a=
 featured NFT was OpenSea=E2=80=99s confidential business information becau=
se it was not publicly available until the featured NFT appeared on the Ope=
nSea website homepage. The value of featured NFTs, as well as other NFTs ma=
de by the same NFT creator, typically appreciated once they appeared on the=
 OpenSea homepage due to the increase in publicity and resulting demand for=
 the NFT.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">From in or about May 2021 to in o=
r about September 2021, NATHANIEL CHASTAIN, the defendant, was responsible =
for selecting the NFTs that would be featured on OpenSea=E2=80=99s homepage=
. =E2=80=A6=C2=A0Employees of OpenSea, including NATHANIEL CHASTAIN, the de=
fendant, had an obligation to maintain the confidentiality of confidential =
business information received in connection with their work for OpenSea, an=
d an obligation to refrain from using such information, except for the bene=
fit of OpenSea or to the extent necessary to perform work for OpenSea. =E2=
=80=A6=C2=A0Indeed, upon joining OpenSea, Chastain signed a written agreeme=
nt in which he acknowledged these obligations.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p sty=
le=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And some examples:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">On August 9, 2021, CHASTAIN purchased ten of the NFT =E2=80=9CFl=
ipping and spinning=E2=80=9D before it was featured on OpenSea=E2=80=99s ho=
mepage, and then sold them at prices 250% to 300% higher than where they we=
re before the NFT was featured..</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On Septemb=
er 14, 2021, CHASTAIN purchased the NFT =E2=80=9CSpectrum of a Ramenficatio=
n Theory,=E2=80=9D as well as three other NFTs by the same creator, shortly=
 before the NFT was featured on OpenSea=E2=80=99s homepage. CHASTAIN made o=
ver four times the amount of money when he sold =E2=80=9CSpectrum of a Rame=
nfication Theory=E2=80=9D early the next morning.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p =
style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t know. You could tell a story abou=
t NFTs that is a story about art? I guess? Like, this guy really liked =E2=
=80=9CSpectrum of a Ramenfication Theory,=E2=80=9D as art? (You can <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27923003.286612/aHR0cHM6L=
y9vcGVuc2VhLmlvL2Fzc2V0cy9ldGhlcmV1bS8weDQ5NWY5NDcyNzY3NDljZTY0NmY2OGFjOGMy=
NDg0MjAwNDVjYjdiNWUvNTMyOTUwNzE4NTYzNjUzNjY5NDAyOTc3MzM3NzY2MDIyMjY3ODUxOTE=
4NjQ0ODY2MDY2OTcxMTg0NTIzMzE5ODM4MzQyMDA0MDgwNzg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1=
e2699a9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;">see it here</a>; it looks like an NFT.) He is an art conno=
isseur-dealer? He was like =E2=80=9Cthis art is beautiful, and I love it, a=
nd I will buy it because I love it, and then I will feature it on our homep=
age because it is so beautiful and I want other people to appreciate its be=
auty=E2=80=9D? Like he decided what would be featured, why not both buy and=
 feature what he loved? And then flip it immediately for a profit, sure, no=
t a great fact. Also:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">To concea=
l his purchase of featured NFTs before they appeared on OpenSea=E2=80=99s h=
omepage, NATHANIEL CHASTAIN, the defendant, used anonymous OpenSea accounts=
, instead of his publicly-known account in his own name, to make the purcha=
ses and sales. He also transferred funds through multiple anonymous Ethereu=
m accounts in order to conceal his involvement in purchasing and selling th=
e featured NFTs.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Seems bad. Bu=
t it is weird to put a person in prison for years because he =E2=80=A6=C2=
=A0bought some internet cartoons =E2=80=A6=C2=A0before =E2=80=A6=C2=A0they =
were =E2=80=A6=C2=A0put on a website? Like on the one hand it certainly see=
ms like insider trading, sure, but on the other hand, does the US governmen=
t have that much interest in protecting the level playing field of trading =
markets in internet cartoons? Were you really <em>defrauded</em>, when you =
sold this guy a copy of =E2=80=9CFlipping and spinning=E2=80=9D at the goin=
g price before he featured it on the homepage? When people worry about insi=
der trading in stocks, it is because they think insider trading undermines =
confidence in the stock market. I feel like everything that has ever been t=
hought, said or done about NFTs undermines confidence in the NFT market, so=
 it=E2=80=99s kind of random to go after this.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;">By the way, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27=
923003.286612/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwM=
jItMDUtMjMvdGhlLXNlYy1nb2VzLWFmdGVyLWdyZWVud2FzaGluZz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNjAyMjJf=
TU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGV=
ybT0yMjA2MDImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBdfc5c=
5a7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> last week I complained</a> about crypto insider trading scand=
