; background-color: #ccc;"> not had a great 2022</a>:</p><blockquote><p sty=
le=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Losses at Tiger Global Management reached 52% this y=
ear, prompting the firm to cut management fees and create separate accounts=
 for the illiquid wagers of customers who want to redeem.=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Tiger Global=E2=80=99s hedge fund sank 14.2% last mont=
h, buffeted by losses in several stocks and substantial markdowns in its pr=
ivate assets, according to an investor letter seen by Bloomberg News and a =
person with knowledge of the matter.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
As the value of its public holdings plummeted, Tiger=E2=80=99s exposure to =
illiquid venture capital bets comprised too much of its portfolio -- leadin=
g the firm to tell investors in its hedge and long-only funds that, if they=
 wish to redeem, their private investments will be placed in a separate acc=
ount that will be cashed out at a later date. The manager is also cutting i=
ts management fees by 50 basis points through December 2023.=C2=A0</p></blo=
ckquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A year ago, in broadly rising tech mar=
kets, Tiger Global <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/27923003.286612/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLz=
IwMjEtMDQtMTUvY29pbmJhc2UtZGlyZWN0LWxpc3RpbmctbmVlZGVkLXRoZS1jb2luLXRpY2tlc=
j9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNjAyMjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9=
bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjA2MDImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cB54bad3f5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> looked sort of like</a> a speeded-up v=
enture capital firm.=C2=A0It made lots of venture investments,=C2=A0but it =
did so in a public-markets-y way: It moved fast, did not spend a long time =
on due diligence, did not want to be highly involved in management or opera=
tions, tried to be fully invested rather than calling capital slowly over t=
ime, and just bought a lot of stuff, making it almost like an index fund fo=
r private tech companies. You could imagine this as a new, more liquid form=
 of venture investing: Tiger Global is a hedge fund, so its investors can g=
et their money back more quickly than a venture capital fund=E2=80=99s inve=
stors, and Tiger=E2=80=99s own investing decisions are quicker and more pub=
lic-markets-y than a venture fund=E2=80=99s would be.</p><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">But that does not work in reverse. Tiger could make private inve=
stments quickly in a boom, but it can=E2=80=99t cash out of them quickly in=
 a bust, which means that its investors can=E2=80=99t cash out quickly eith=
er.=C2=A0</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacin=
